86.3	Measles	Measles	Measles, also known as morbilli, is an infection of the respiratory system caused by a virus, specifically a paramyxovirus of the genus Morbillivirus. Morbilliviruses, like other paramyxoviruses, are enveloped, single-stranded, negative-sense RNA viruses. Symptoms include fever, cough, runny nose, red eyes and a generalized, maculopapular, erythematous rash.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Measles_virus.JPG/230px-Measles_virus.JPG
